1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:02,460
Um...

2
00:00:02,460 --> 00:00:05,990
You're challenging 100?! That's impossible!

3
00:00:05,990 --> 00:00:09,610
It isn't set up for one 
person to destroy them all!

4
00:00:09,910 --> 00:00:11,030
I don't care.

5
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:51,460
The competition for day three is Pandemonium.

6
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:56,620
It's a contest to see who can slay the 
most out of 100 magic-generated monsters.

7
00:01:57,050 --> 00:01:59,810
The contestants enter one at a time

8
00:01:59,810 --> 00:02:01,560
and indicate the number of 
monsters they aim to defeat.

9
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:04,160
They get points by successfully 
beating the beasts.

10
00:02:04,610 --> 00:02:07,720
The idea is to repeatedly rotate 
through the players, but...

11
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:11,650
All 100 will be my opponents!

12
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:14,000
I exercise my right to challenge...

13
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:16,640
...100!

14
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:25,490
This beyond-foolhardy challenge 
is about to begin.

15
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:34,980
100 to 1!

16
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:42,440
Erza!

17
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:45,220
The inside is pretty big...

18
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:47,470
But it's upside down...

19
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,650
It makes me sick just lookin' at it!

20
00:02:51,610 --> 00:02:55,610
I'm Erza Scarlet from Fairy Tail A.

21
00:02:57,650 --> 00:03:00,200
I challenge 100.

22
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:13,100
A bunch have come out...

23
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:16,110
Even the D-class ones looked 
really strong, right?

24
00:03:16,110 --> 00:03:20,240
Does she really mean to take 
all of them on by herself?

25
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:22,610
She does. Erza means it.

26
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:24,070
I can understand.

27
00:03:24,070 --> 00:03:27,050
Natsu, you seem to be having fun.

28
00:03:27,050 --> 00:03:29,520
Maybe you were a better fit for 
this than that Chariot event.

29
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:32,370
Will Erza-san be alright?

30
00:03:32,370 --> 00:03:34,070
I'm sure she'll get through it.

31
00:03:34,070 --> 00:03:36,940
Well, it should be a spectacle, anyway.

32
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:39,900
She's as reckless as always...

33
00:03:40,950 --> 00:03:43,910
She hasn't changed a bit 
in the past seven years.

34
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:47,920
Requip!

35
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:52,210
Heaven's Wheel!

36
00:03:52,330 --> 00:03:54,000
Blumenblatt!

37
00:03:59,350 --> 00:04:03,330
Whoa! Erza has carried out a preemptive 
strike with an omni-directional attack!

38
00:04:03,330 --> 00:04:07,230
The D-class monsters are 
dropping one after another!

39
00:04:08,870 --> 00:04:11,350
Was she trying to demolish them all at once?

40
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,510
No.

41
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,950
By doing an omni-directional attack,

42
00:04:14,950 --> 00:04:19,270
she learned the responses, the abilities, 
and the defensive capabilities of each type.

43
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:25,180
Also, in an instant, she was able 
to calculate which armor to use

44
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:27,360
against each kind of monster.

45
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:34,390
Her attacking power has improved!

46
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:35,950
Black Wing Armor!

47
00:04:35,950 --> 00:04:39,110
With each strike, its power increases!

48
00:04:39,110 --> 00:04:43,360
Then she's starting out by reducing 
their numbers with sheer force, huh?

49
00:04:46,850 --> 00:04:48,220
Erza-san!

50
00:04:48,220 --> 00:04:49,900
It breathes fire!

51
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:52,920
No worries! If the enemy's fire...

52
00:04:52,990 --> 00:04:55,890
Oh, that's right! She's 
got Flame Empress Armor!

53
00:04:58,440 --> 00:05:00,320
She brushed the flames aside!

54
00:05:00,350 --> 00:05:01,610
What is that?!

55
00:05:01,610 --> 00:05:04,310
A weapon that's part of a set 
with her Sea Empress Armor!

56
00:05:04,310 --> 00:05:06,610
Water against flames, right?

57
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:16,460
Oh, my! She's destroyed five 
C-class monsters already!

58
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,790
Uh-oh! What's this?!

59
00:05:27,570 --> 00:05:29,970
A fire and water dual-sword technique?

60
00:05:29,970 --> 00:05:32,220
But it also looks like 
she took some damage...

61
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:37,260
So you're S-class...

62
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:39,150
No, that's not right.

63
00:05:43,570 --> 00:05:47,540
She returned fire against the water enemy 
with Sea Empress Armor and a lightning attack!

64
00:05:47,540 --> 00:05:48,750
Correct!

65
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:50,820
Fast judgment...

66
00:05:51,170 --> 00:05:53,910
And the confidence to back it up...

67
00:05:58,270 --> 00:06:00,500
She's a wonderful wizard, isn't she?

68
00:06:01,550 --> 00:06:03,690
Th-This is awesome!

69
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:06,450
She's already cut down half of the monsters!

70
00:06:06,470 --> 00:06:07,590
Seriously?!

71
00:06:07,590 --> 00:06:09,220
That's Erza for you.

72
00:06:09,220 --> 00:06:12,930
Her every move is polished, 
with not a movement wasted.

73
00:06:12,930 --> 00:06:15,750
I wonder if Sho and Wally 
are watching, too...

74
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,360
Nonsense!

75
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,170
Is this really anything 
to make a fuss about?!

76
00:06:19,530 --> 00:06:21,720
Look at her! She's all beat up!

77
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:24,900
It does look like she's exhausted...

78
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:29,040
Go, Erza! Smash 'em to pieces!

79
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,870
I don't know...

80
00:06:30,870 --> 00:06:33,160
It looks like she's kind 
of having a hard time...

81
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:53,970
Oh, boy! Even wounded, Erza smoothly 
dispatched a succession of monsters,

82
00:06:53,970 --> 00:06:57,220
but now she's facing an A-class monster!

83
00:06:58,870 --> 00:07:01,540
That looked like a heavy hit!

84
00:07:01,540 --> 00:07:03,680
Ah! Hit that badly...

85
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:08,900
No. Just the opposite. I 
believe she used its weight.

86
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:06,270
The terrifying Titania!

87
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:09,540
She requips over and over,

88
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:12,210
steadily crushing the monsters!

89
00:08:12,210 --> 00:08:15,480
While she's taken damage and 
depleted a lot of her magic,

90
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:18,980
unbelievably... just four monsters are left!

91
00:08:18,980 --> 00:08:21,380
But those are all strong ones!

92
00:08:21,380 --> 00:08:25,480
And she hasn't defeated 
the S-class monster yet...

93
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:27,840
S-class, my ass!

94
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:32,070
We know just how awesome S-class Erza is!

95
00:08:36,260 --> 00:08:37,740
Hey, she...

96
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:09,650
And finally... And finally, the last one!

97
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:13,800
Just what kind of monster is an S-class one?!

98
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,740
Uh... Huh?

99
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:16,960
I thought so.

100
00:09:17,350 --> 00:09:19,030
So you're the S-class, huh?

101
00:09:19,030 --> 00:09:20,450
What?!

102
00:09:20,450 --> 00:09:21,630
It's tiny!

103
00:09:21,630 --> 00:09:24,460
What a cute monster-san!

104
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:28,590
Still, I have a bad feeling about this...

105
00:09:29,410 --> 00:09:32,670
Huh? Why is Erza-nee changing her sword?

106
00:09:32,670 --> 00:09:35,000
From Benizakura to two swords?

107
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,140
Against that puny foe?

108
00:09:37,140 --> 00:09:38,820
Something must be up...

109
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:41,390
Yeah. Look at her expression.

110
00:09:41,390 --> 00:09:44,220
Her concentration and sense 
of tension have doubled!

111
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:46,180
Come.

112
00:09:58,510 --> 00:10:02,230
This is why I told you 
it was impossible-kabo!

113
00:10:02,230 --> 00:10:06,220
It's set up so that when the S-class monster

114
00:10:06,220 --> 00:10:10,910
becomes the last one left, 
its power triples-kabo!

115
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:14,350
Alright! Pandemonium's last monster!

116
00:10:14,350 --> 00:10:18,830
But somehow the battle 
has moved to the arena!

117
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:24,050
The now super-sized S-class 
monster is bearing down on Erza!

118
00:10:24,310 --> 00:10:27,900
Who knew they set it up like this?

119
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:29,760
An unexpected ambush...

120
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:33,600
I see. Fitting for a place 
called "Pandemonium"...

121
00:10:35,190 --> 00:10:39,760
Go! That giant thing is 
no match for you, Erza!

122
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:55,800
The third day of the Grand Magic Games...

123
00:10:56,100 --> 00:10:57,630
Pandemonium.

124
00:10:58,530 --> 00:11:02,640
I don't think I'll ever forget this day...

125
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,930
Even while being badly wounded,

126
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:10,800
a fairy that should've 
fallen to the ground...

127
00:11:11,390 --> 00:11:12,060
...soared.

128
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:15,650
Titania...

129
00:11:15,890 --> 00:11:16,940
Here you are.

130
00:11:32,490 --> 00:11:34,130
Just like...

131
00:11:34,540 --> 00:11:37,520
...a dignified scarlet 
flower in all its glory.

132
00:11:41,510 --> 00:11:44,530
U-Unbelievable!

133
00:11:44,530 --> 00:11:49,850
Amazingly, Erza has obliterated 
100 monsters all by herself!

134
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:53,710
Erza Scarlet of Fairy Tail A has 
scored a resounding victory!

135
00:11:53,710 --> 00:11:56,810
Without any question, a tremendous win!

136
00:11:57,160 --> 00:12:01,030
Is this the true strength of the guild 
that was called the most powerful

137
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:03,810
seven years ago?!

138
00:12:11,870 --> 00:12:13,250
A-Awesome!

139
00:12:13,250 --> 00:12:14,880
What is she?!

140
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,200
I remember her!

141
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:19,950
Fairy Tail's strongest 
woman wizard, Erza Scarlet!

142
00:12:19,950 --> 00:12:23,510
Yeah, Titania! Erza!

143
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:27,180
The cheering just won't stop!

144
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:29,220
I give up...

145
00:12:29,340 --> 00:12:30,820
I don't have the words...

146
00:12:31,660 --> 00:12:34,030
Her rash action...

147
00:12:34,380 --> 00:12:37,630
I couldn't see that it would lead to this...

148
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:39,840
Erza!

149
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,240
Guys...

150
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,810
Sorry.

151
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,450
It took longer than I thought it would.

152
00:12:45,450 --> 00:12:46,110
Ow!

153
00:12:46,350 --> 00:12:48,070
You were great!

154
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:49,580
Fight me later!

155
00:12:48,070 --> 00:12:49,750
I was moved!

156
00:12:49,750 --> 00:12:52,010
I've got a lump in my throat...

157
00:12:52,010 --> 00:12:55,450
Come on... It's not like 
we won the tournament yet.

158
00:12:57,130 --> 00:12:58,580
Excuse me...

159
00:12:58,830 --> 00:13:02,160
You said it took longer 
than you thought it would?

160
00:13:03,090 --> 00:13:05,170
Nobody holds a candle to her.

161
00:13:05,170 --> 00:13:07,750
Er-chan really is the most powerful!

162
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:09,470
The spiffiest and most powerful!

163
00:13:09,470 --> 00:13:12,350
I should've expected no less 
of Ichiya-san's girlfriend...

164
00:13:12,550 --> 00:13:14,630
She blazes as brightly as the sun!

165
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:19,370
I guess seeing that makes 
a guy say reckless things!

166
00:13:19,370 --> 00:13:20,140
Marvelous.

167
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:22,900
I don't like this...

168
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:26,610
Erza! Erza! Erza! Erza!

169
00:13:26,610 --> 00:13:29,570
Erza! Erza! Erza! Erza!

170
00:13:29,570 --> 00:13:31,700
I knew you could do it, Erza!

171
00:13:29,570 --> 00:13:34,580
Erza! Erza! Erza! Erza!

172
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:32,910
Yay!

173
00:13:32,910 --> 00:13:35,040
I-I love you!

174
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:38,320
Fairy Tail has been booed since day one!

175
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:41,500
But this wild applause makes 
that almost hard to believe!

176
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:45,010
After seeing her, anybody would applaud...

177
00:13:45,010 --> 00:13:48,090
To be honest, I was moved as well.

178
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:51,110
The seven years that were lost...

179
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:52,460
Yeesh...

180
00:13:52,550 --> 00:13:54,970
It looks like I don't have 
to worry about it anymore...

181
00:13:55,350 --> 00:14:00,760
Th-That's no big deal! We 
could've done the same thing!

182
00:14:00,780 --> 00:14:04,110
F-Fro thinks so, too...

183
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:05,220
Interesting.

184
00:14:05,710 --> 00:14:08,760
I suppose you aren't all talk,

185
00:14:08,850 --> 00:14:10,200
Fairy Tail...

186
00:14:10,460 --> 00:14:12,720
She's incredible...

187
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:15,700
I've never seen anything like that before...

188
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:19,100
I guess they don't call her 
"Titania" for nothing...

189
00:14:20,170 --> 00:14:22,180
Erza Scarlet...

190
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:24,380
You know Jellal well...

191
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:27,580
Pandemonium has been conquered!

192
00:14:27,580 --> 00:14:31,120
Fairy Tail A receives ten points!

193
00:14:35,130 --> 00:14:41,230
After some discussion, it's been decided 
that the other seven teams need to be ranked,

194
00:14:41,230 --> 00:14:46,150
so this is somewhat of a drag, but 
a simple game has been prepared.

195
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:47,630
What is this?

196
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:49,960
A Magic Power Finder!

197
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:52,130
In short, MPF!

198
00:14:52,130 --> 00:14:55,160
A device to measure magic...

199
00:14:55,170 --> 00:14:56,430
Exactly.

200
00:14:56,780 --> 00:15:02,240
When this machine is hit with magic, the 
magic power will be displayed as a numeral value.

201
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:05,990
Those values will be 
ranked, from high to low.

202
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:08,810
A simple test of strength, huh?

203
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:11,310
I'm at kind of a disadvantage here...

204
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:14,920
By the way, Cana-san, are you free tonight?

205
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:19,720
I'm free, but I don't think I'll be 
able to drink more than one barrel...

206
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:21,100
You drink too much!

207
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:22,800
That's an understatement!

208
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:24,780
That drunk!

209
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:26,740
That's no good...

210
00:15:26,740 --> 00:15:31,010
Cana-san! The competition isn't over yet!

211
00:15:31,670 --> 00:15:33,540
Alright, let's begin!

212
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:36,870
We'll go with the order that 
was decided before-kabo!

213
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:39,120
Then I'm up first!

214
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:41,620
Here I go!

215
00:15:41,620 --> 00:15:45,460
Oh, my! Under the cloak is a daring outfit!

216
00:15:45,460 --> 00:15:47,880
Kitten Blast!

217
00:15:49,060 --> 00:15:51,390
The value is 365!

218
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:55,140
But that being said,

219
00:15:55,140 --> 00:15:59,740
without a benchmark to compare it to, we 
don't know if this is a high score or not...

220
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:05,310
We Rune Knights also use the 
MPF as part of our training.

221
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:07,520
This number is a high score.

222
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:09,880
A level high enough to 
make someone a captain.

223
00:16:10,690 --> 00:16:12,740
Then that's an impressive figure, isn't it?!

224
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:14,750
Feelin' spiffy!

225
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:18,680
Although Millianna's real 
strength isn't about power...

226
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:21,390
She may be at a disadvantage here...

227
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:24,670
Next is Quatro Puppy's Novale!

228
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:28,050
His value is 124! Seems a little low...

229
00:16:29,620 --> 00:16:31,460
It's my turn, huh?

230
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:35,810
This is a tough one for Hibiki, whose 
magic is the intellectual type.

231
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,760
I should've done this one...

232
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:40,810
Believe in your friend, you two.

233
00:16:40,810 --> 00:16:42,960
Master! When did you get here?!

234
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:45,470
So you're back in action, huh, senpai?

235
00:16:46,180 --> 00:16:48,610
Jenny passed me the baton.

236
00:16:50,140 --> 00:16:54,060
Hibiki of Blue Pegasus! 
His magic power is 95...

237
00:16:54,770 --> 00:16:56,110
That's terrible...

238
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:58,800
Is this what we get for believing in him?

239
00:16:59,970 --> 00:17:04,210
Men... But there's a lot 
to learn from failure.

240
00:17:04,260 --> 00:17:07,320
You can take this and strive 
to do better, for example.

241
00:17:07,340 --> 00:17:09,750
Right! Your words are sweet 
music to our ears, Sensei!

242
00:17:11,110 --> 00:17:13,750
He's already striving...

243
00:17:11,490 --> 00:17:14,710
Want me to comfort you tonight?

244
00:17:14,360 --> 00:17:16,250
Um...

245
00:17:14,710 --> 00:17:16,760
I want you to baby me now...

246
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:19,890
Next up is Obra of Raven Tail!

247
00:17:20,150 --> 00:17:21,300
That's the guy...

248
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:23,250
...who attacked Carla and Wendy!

249
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:23,960
Right...

250
00:17:24,490 --> 00:17:26,060
Raven, huh?

251
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:28,210
I wonder what kind of magic he'll use...

252
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:34,360
What the...?! His magic power is 4!

253
00:17:34,710 --> 00:17:35,950
Is he just messin' around?

254
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:39,020
What's with that guy?!

255
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:42,330
And shouldn't you be in the infirmary?

256
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:47,420
That's a little unfortunate, but 
there are no do-overs here-kabo...

257
00:17:48,970 --> 00:17:50,710
Um, excuse me...

258
00:17:51,050 --> 00:17:54,690
Jeez! Obra, what the hell are you doing?!

259
00:17:54,690 --> 00:17:56,370
Are you an idiot?!

260
00:17:56,370 --> 00:17:57,820
Silence, Flare.

261
00:17:57,820 --> 00:18:00,710
His magic can't be shown in front of people.

262
00:18:00,710 --> 00:18:02,050
Y-Yes, sir.

263
00:18:02,050 --> 00:18:05,540
He's a guy who's gotta 
be forced to get serious.

264
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:07,980
Alright,

265
00:18:07,980 --> 00:18:12,900
currently the top score is 365 from 
Millianna of Mermaid Heel-kabo!

266
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:16,250
Yay! I'm number one!

267
00:18:16,250 --> 00:18:18,330
We'll see about that...

268
00:18:18,830 --> 00:18:22,540
Sabertooth's Orga takes the field!

269
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:24,060
Listen to those cheers!

270
00:18:24,450 --> 00:18:27,520
Orga-kun! Please win this thing!

271
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:29,450
Orga's strong, isn't he?

272
00:18:30,010 --> 00:18:33,050
120mm Black Lightning Cannon!

273
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:39,090
O-Over 3,000?!

274
00:18:39,910 --> 00:18:41,640
Ten times my score?!

275
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:43,070
Wha...?!

276
00:18:43,070 --> 00:18:44,680
What the hell is that?!

277
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:45,610
Wow...

278
00:18:46,370 --> 00:18:49,500
I've never seen a score like 
that, not even in my Corps!

279
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:53,550
That's Orga-kun! When it comes 
to power, he's the strongest!

280
00:18:53,550 --> 00:18:55,840
Fro thinks so, too!

281
00:18:56,980 --> 00:19:00,740
The strongest, the strongest, number one!

282
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:02,390
We don't need to hear 
any more singing-kabo...

283
00:19:00,740 --> 00:19:04,550
Our guild, Sabertooth, kicks 
the ass of everyone!

284
00:19:03,190 --> 00:19:07,890
Alright, can Jura, one of the 10 Great 
Wizard Saints, surpass this score?

285
00:19:07,890 --> 00:19:09,250
He's got everyone's attention!

286
00:19:09,510 --> 00:19:11,930
Jura-san will win, won't he?

287
00:19:11,930 --> 00:19:15,700
Of course. I'm concerned 
about something else.

288
00:19:16,650 --> 00:19:19,200
Do you mind if I do this seriously?

289
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,200
Go right ahead-kabo!

290
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:25,090
It appears that Jura of Lamia 
Scale is concentrating!

291
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,110
An earthquake!

292
00:19:30,150 --> 00:19:32,520
We're feeling tremendous pressure...

293
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,190
Rumbling Mt. Fuji!

294
00:19:41,650 --> 00:19:46,570
8,544! Unbelievable!

295
00:19:46,570 --> 00:19:47,410
What?!

296
00:19:47,410 --> 00:19:50,000
Old man, that's wack!

297
00:19:50,330 --> 00:19:52,140
In a word, unsurprising.

298
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:54,490
Those nicknamed the 10 Great Wizard Saints

299
00:19:54,490 --> 00:19:59,600
are just so powerful. Shouldn't 
their participation be limited?

300
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:02,310
I see. So that's what you're 
worried about, Lyon.

301
00:20:02,660 --> 00:20:06,120
Th-This is a new record for the MPF!

302
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:09,560
The title "10 Great Wizard 
Saints" isn't just for show!

303
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:12,150
This blows me away...

304
00:20:12,150 --> 00:20:14,620
He's probably evenly matched with Gildarts...

305
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:20,110
Don't forget that someone who shares 
Gildarts' blood is right over there.

306
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:25,480
And our final challenger is 
Cana Alberona of Fairy Tail B!

307
00:20:26,650 --> 00:20:29,030
So it's finally my turn?

308
00:20:29,030 --> 00:20:32,360
I'm sure it's tough to follow Jura, but...

309
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:34,970
Well, just do your best-kabo.

310
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,200
She's smashed...

311
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:40,540
Is she gonna try to get into 
the thousands in that state?

312
00:20:40,540 --> 00:20:44,130
I predict in the high hundreds 
for a third place finish...

313
00:20:45,940 --> 00:20:47,510
But why is she stripping?!

314
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:51,020
Alright, I'm gonna hit you hard!

315
00:20:51,790 --> 00:20:53,140
That emblem!

316
00:20:53,140 --> 00:20:55,380
D-Don't tell me...

317
00:20:55,530 --> 00:20:57,940
I lent it to her just this once...

318
00:20:58,490 --> 00:21:00,270
...so she could win!

319
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:03,960
Gather!

320
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:07,200
River of light that guides fairies!

321
00:21:07,630 --> 00:21:09,760
In the first place, that woman

322
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:12,630
has incredibly high latent ability.

323
00:21:13,110 --> 00:21:15,710
So I'm sure she'll be able to master this.

324
00:21:15,710 --> 00:21:19,140
Shine! To destroy the fangs of evil!

325
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:23,820
Fairy Glitter!

326
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:28,810
That Cana possesses one of the 
Three Great Fairy Magics?

327
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:33,120
O-Oh my goodness!

328
00:21:33,120 --> 00:21:36,340
The MPF is destroyed! The counter's stopped!

329
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:39,100
What is this guild?!

330
00:21:39,650 --> 00:21:42,020
It's a one-two finish for 
the competition part!

331
00:21:42,020 --> 00:21:46,610
Can anyone stop Fairy Tail now?!

332
00:21:46,610 --> 00:21:48,320
We're unstoppable!

333
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:52,560
It's because we're Fairy Tail, see?!

334
00:21:57,740 --> 00:22:01,780
I need to think a bit-kabo...

335
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:04,020
Alexei-sama...

336
00:22:04,020 --> 00:22:06,320
Here's the list of battle matches...

337
00:22:07,570 --> 00:22:09,730
This match-up...

338
00:22:09,730 --> 00:22:13,030
The management is well-informed.

339
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:16,040
Shall we begin?

340
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:19,600
For the sake of our true purpose...

341
00:23:55,690 --> 00:23:58,190
F-F-Feelin' spiffy!

342
00:24:00,270 --> 00:24:01,590
What are you doing?

343
00:24:01,590 --> 00:24:03,700
I thought up a Mini Anna cheer song!

344
00:24:03,700 --> 00:24:06,920
Natsu, it's "Millianna", not "Mini Anna"!

345
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:08,290
And she's on a rival team!

346
00:24:08,290 --> 00:24:11,870
Well, I could go on, but 
first off, why a song?

347
00:24:11,870 --> 00:24:13,840
I'm sick of cheering the usual way.

348
00:24:13,850 --> 00:24:16,710
Next time: Laxus vs. Alexei!

349
00:24:16,710 --> 00:24:21,620
I am the king of crackling lightning...

350
00:24:21,660 --> 00:24:24,110
Don't tell me that's your 
cheer song for Laxus?!

